The right to issue the order lays in hands ofspecific regional authority, based on the permanent residence of the student. Once being selected, the order will be sent to you. Work duty could be ordered at any time during the state of emergency.

Travels related to work duty are exempt from the ban on free movement.

Thank you for your help during these tough times.

4k.title: Psychological help for children and students
4k.content:
Recommendation

Apandemic is adifficult time for everyone, so it is normal not to feel well.

Recommendations in Czech for teenagers were prepared by the organization Nevypus큐 Du큄i.

You can learn more about the basic recommendations for psycho-hygiene during apandemic in Stress and handling impactsof apandemic section.

If necessary, contact one of the lines taught for children and young people:

  • Line of Safety (Association of Lines of Safety): 116 111 (nonstop), FREE help for children, young people, and students under 26 years of age
  • Children'sCrisis Center Helpline: 777 715 215, 241 484 149 (nonstop) for children and adults
  • Crisis line SOS center Diakonie: 800 567 567 (daily 9-20), FREE

4l.title: Psychological help for parents
4l.content:
Recommendations for handling the state of emergency

Being in some form of isolation or quarantine can be very challenging. If possible, still maintain your social contacts through the online world during this time. Try to keep your own habits and as constant as possible. It is important to eat in abalanced way, to have enough sleep and rest, and also to strive for physical and mental activity. It'sagood idea to use stress management methods that have worked for you before and have proven to be effective. There are many ways to reduce stress, such as relaxation or meditation.

You can learn about the basic recommendations for maintaining mental health in the Mental hygiene section.

If you feel that you need to talk to someone, either about aspecific problem or just to talk, contact one of the crisis lines. You can find alist of them in thePsychological help section.

Recommendations for managing cohabitation in an emergency

Spending quarantine in acouple or family can be an advantage and adisadvantage. You and your partner and family can support each other, but there is also arisk that in time you will "start getting on each other'snerves."

What to do to avoid conflicts?

  • It is essential to arm yourself with adose of patience and tolerance - with apandemic, the dynamics of your coexistence are likely to change significantly, and it will take everyone along time to come to terms with the situation.
  • Try to divide the time into the time spent on joint activities and the time that each of you devotes to yourself.
  • If there are also children in the household, try to divide taking care of them.
  • These times are also demanding in terms of worries and fears - about the health of loved ones, about the future. Try to talk to your partner about your concerns.
  • Do not bottle your feelings inside, try, and talk about them with your partner and children. If you resolve the dispute right away, the situation is far less likely to escalate.
  • Remember that the situation also affects children. They don'tsee friends, they have nowhere to exhaust their energy. If you suddenly find the space of the apartment smaller than usual, try to go for awalk in the fresh air. Ashort walk will certainly benefit you.
  • Have some fun - watch amovie, cook with your family or play aboard game.

4m.title: Hunting
4m.content:
The exercise of the right to hunt is an exception to the measures taken by the Government of the Czech Republic and is therefore permitted.

Joint and individual hunting is allowed in order to comply with the hunting plan and to prevent damage to the deer (e.g.joint hunting of small deer).All hunting exams are not allowed.

In the case of joint hunting, the spacing must be observed and the face mask fitted. The measures taken do not allow for hunting exams or social events

4n.title: Domestic violence prevention
4n.content:
Recommendations

If you feel threatened by your partner or another household memberdue to mental, physical or sexual violence or coercion, immediately contact the helpline for domestic violence.

  • Crime and Domestic Violence Helpline White Circle of Safety: 116 006 (non-stop), FREE help for victims.
  • Helpline for victims of domestic and sexual violence proFem +420 608 222 277, social worker - Monday to Friday from 9am to15pm, the legal helpline for victims of domestic and sexual violence - Tuesday from 9amto 12pmand Wednesday from 5:30pm to 8:30pm.
  • ROSA helplinefor victims of domestic violence: +420241432 466(mon, tue9:00-18:00, wed, thu from 9am to 4pm, fri from 9am to 2pm,SOS line:+420 602 246 102(mon-frifrom 9am to 6pm, +420 739 709 764(mon, tuefrom 9am to 6pmwed, thufrom 9am to 4pm, fri from9am to 2pm).

In case of adirect threat, please contact Police of the Czech Republicon line 158.

4o.title: After-school activities
4o.content:
Rules and recommendation

The presence of children in after-school activities is temporarily banned.

Exemption to the ban is presence on individual consultations orclasses (one teacher on one student) if hygiene standards are fulfilled.

4p.title: Students: the return home
4p.content:
Rules and recommendations

Accommodation in student housing and dormitories is restricted at the moment. Students currently resident in the Czech republic without valid exception have to return home.

If you are going home to your family, you can use the option of Covid- 19 testing without delay by one of the mobile testing teams. Please wait for the results of your test in isolation to prevent possible contact of your loved ones with someone Covid-positive.

If the result of your test is positive, it would be best to wait for your quarantine out in your dormitory room. We recommend the same approach if you are already in quarantine. Finish your quarantine in your dormitory and visit your family afterward.

If you suffer from any psychological difficulties related to isolation, fear of the illness, or fear for your loved ones, check the section Stress and handling impacts ofthe pandemic.

After returning home the student is seen as amember of the household that he has returned to. Governmental regulations for members of one household apply to them.

4q.title: Cohabitation in the state of emergency
4q.content:
Recommendations for surviving in the state of emergency

Being in some form of isolation or quarantine can be very challenging. If possible, keep your social contacts through the online platforms during this time. Try to keep your habits and routines as constant as possible. It is important to eat balanced meals, have enough sleep and rest, and also aim for physical and mental activity. It is agood idea to keep using stress management methods that have worked for you before and have proven to be effective. There are many ways to reduce stress, such as relaxation or meditation.

You can learn about the fundamental recommendations for maintaining mental health in section Stress and handling the impacts of the pandemic > Mental hygiene.

If you feel that you need to talk to someone, either about aspecific problem or just to be in contact with someone, reach to one of the crisis lines. You can find alist of them in section Stress and handling the impacts of the pandemic > Psychological help.

Recommendations for coping with cohabitation in the state of emergency

Spending quarantine in acouple or with family can be an advantage as well as adisadvantage. You and your partner and family can support each other, but there is also arisk that in some time, you will "start getting on each other'snerves."

What to do to avoid conflicts?

  1. It is essential to arm yourself with adose of patience and tolerance - with apandemic, the dynamics of your coexistence are likely to change, and it takes everyone some time to come to terms with the situation.
  2. Try to divide the time into the time spent on joint activities and the time for yourself.
  3. If there are children in your household, try to divide the care equivalently.
  4. These times can also be exhausting in terms of your worries. You can have concerns about the health of loved ones or the future. Try to open to your partner and talk about your anxieties.
  5. Do not stifle your feelings inside of you and try to talk about them with your partner and children. If you resolve disputes straight away, there is far less risk that the situation would escalate.
  6. Remember that the situation also affects children. They cannot see their friends, and they do not have that many options where to drain their energy. If you suddenly find the space in your apartment smaller than usual, try to go for awalk on the fresh air. Ashort walk will surely help you.
  7. Have some fun - watch amovie, cook with your family or play aboard game.

4r.title: Libraries
4r.content:
Rules and recommendations

The library services are limited.

It is forbidden to receive or return books in other way than contactless. Libraries can operate, for example, through apop-up window. You can borrow just pre-ordered books.

If you need to know what exact lending rules each library has set, follow their websites.

If you need books - whether for study, work or entertainment - try the electronic resources database. Follow the offer of electronic resources on the websitesof each library. For university students, universities usually offer access to these databases for free. Look for these options on the websites of universities or faculties.

4s.title: Chess
4s.content:
Rules and recommendations

Currently, all chess events are prohibited.

The measure concerns both long-term competitions under the Chess Association of the Czech Republic (first, second, and third national league) and competitions organized by individual regional associations (competitions from the regional championship below).

No tournaments can be held.

4t.title: Children쨈sassociations
4t.content:
All children쨈sassociation (scout, pioneer,...) events are strictly forbidden at the moment.

Only volunteering is allowed.

4u.title: I쨈mateacher
4u.content:
Rules and recommendations

It goes without saying that you can attend school, if you are ateacher of students that take part in the full-time teaching. In this case, observe the hygiene recommendations and measures:

  • Face masks are compulsory for both students and teachers.
  • We recommend frequent ventilation in classrooms and common areas (5minutes between hours and in the middle of each hour, or every 30 minutes).
  • It is recommended to stay on the fresh air as much as possible.
  • We recommend organizing the movement of students within the school area (including arrival and departure) so as to limit the contact.
  • Singing and sports activities are prohibited.

Home office is recommended for all pedagogical professions. Therefore, you should provide an online teaching from your home. However, if you do not have the necessary equipment at home, it is possible to go to school and teach from an empty classroom or your cabinet. However, please observe the increased hygiene measures, especially the Wear Z (face masks, social distance and disinfect your hands).

Distance learning is not only acomplex challenge for students, but also for teachers. Many of us are just learning how to use the online tools. It is agood opportunity for you to learn something new and expand your skills as well as helping your students. The teacher'sinterpretation is irreplaceable during the study and students will certainly appreciate your effort to mediate it, at least remotely.

The current situation is very demanding. Especially with the increased stress that achange in the type of teaching entails. Don'tbe afraid to ask for help. See Stress and Pandemic Impact Management for more information.

If you need technical help, perhaps you can ask your children for help/or even students. They will be happy to help you and pass on their experience.

Inspiration

On the website of the Ministry of Education, Youth and Sports, you will find alot of useful tips for online teaching.

4v.title: Beekeepers
4v.content:
All adopted measures (ban on the free movement of people, ban on organizing events, etc.) apply to beekeepers without exception.

However, no measures have been taken regarding the breeding itself, so all procedures, processes, and registration remain unchanged.

4w.title: Blood donators
4w.content:
Rules and recommendations

Donating blood is as important in times of pandemic as in times without crisis. Particularly rare blood groups AB and Bare long-term deficient.

For more information about blood donation

Conditions for blood donation

List of transfusion stations

Donation of convalescent plasma COVID-19

If you have recently had COVID-19 and want to help patients with severe symptoms, you can donate blood plasma. It contains protein antibodies and can help save lives.

List of collection points

4x.title: Financial gifts
4x.content:
Who to support?

At the times of the global pandemicdonation ofany funds can be very helpful. Supportingany areas and fields affected or exhausted by the current situationis welcomed.

Youcan supportmedical staff in hospitalsor helpschool facilitiesafford thepurchase of electronic equipment for online teaching, ordonate to many trustworthy projects and initiatives.

Think carefully though, and choose wisely whom you ultimately fund. Even during acrisis like this, there isanumber of people who might take advantage of your good intentions.

4y.title: Shared household
4y.content:
Recommendations

If you live in ashared household, where roommates have different jobs and therefore spend time in other groups of people, please pay increased attention to hygiene recommendations and often ventilate.

If you share the household with aperson who is in the high-risk group (elderly, chronically ill, or aperson with weakened immunity), be responsible and try to protect them from the infection.

The lower number of social contacts you have, the lower possibility of the infection in your house.

4z.title: Electronical gifts
4z.content:
Opportunities

We are currently experiencing avery challenging period associated with many challenging life situations. One of them may be the lack of an opportunity for households to prepare for an online lifestyle.

These are mainly children from socially disadvantaged or multiple-membered families who cannot attend distance learning, for example, due to alack of internet connection, not owning acomputer or tablet from which to connect. Therefore, if someone has acomputer, laptop, or tablet that they do not need, provide it to afamily or school facility where they will find agreat use for it.

If you do not know any family in need in your area, contact the nearest schools. They will advise you on how to proceed. Several initiatives address this issue. Specifically, for example, Computers for childrenor We teach online.

5a.title: Courts
5a.content:
Rules and Recommendations

The courts continue functioning even in times of emergency, but it'snecessary to follow the general rules, especially to observe hygienic measures (wear aface mask, social distance, and disinfect your hands), give priority to written communication, and follow the rules of conduct in the courthouse.

Court proceedings may take place, but judges should consider the epidemiological situation, the urgency of the proceedings (time limits), and the need for apersonal presence at the hearing when the ruling is made.

The public may be present at the trial but must wear aface mask at all times. This will protect themselves and others in the courtroom.

When visiting the courts, it is necessary to follow increased hygienic measures - the court building can only be entered after prior hand disinfection. At the entrance to the courthouse, you may be asked to provide astatement that you do not have an infectious disease, fever, or symptoms of respiratory disease (especially coughing, sneezing, breathing difficulties).

It is necessary to wear aface mask in the court building at all times. Exceptions to the obligation to wear aface mask at the time of court proceedings apply to judges and jurors, public prosecutors, the accused, their lawyer, hearing participants and their representatives, witnesses, court experts, translators, and other persons for whom the court allows not to wear aface mask.

Inspection of the files is possible only in necessary cases (e.g.if the statutory deadline was missed or in the case of ordered proceedings) and after prior agreement.

Prefer written or electronic communication with the courts. An online data-box can also be used to communicate with the courts.

Specific courts can take their own measures, which can be found on the website of aspecific court.

5b.title: The return home
5b.content:
Rules and recommendations

The operation of accommodation on university dormitories is limited. Students who do not meet the special conditions (explained in more detail in the Halls of residencesection) must return home to their place of residence.

If you are returning home to your family, take advantage of immediate testing on Covid-19 through mobile testing facilities. Please wait for the test result in isolation to prevent possible contact with the infected person and subsequent transmission to your loved ones.

In the case of apositive test result, we recommend spending your quarantine in the student dormitory area. We recommend the same procedure if you are already in quarantine. Finish your quarantine in the dormitory and then go home to your family.

In case of mental problems associated with isolation, fear of illness, or concern for loved ones, use the information from the Stress and handling the impacts of pandemic section.

After returning home, the student is perceived as amember of the household to which they returned. Therefore, follow the government'smeasures that apply to members of one household.

5c.title: Retail
5c.content:
Rules and recommendations

All retail is closed in general.

Only shops carrying essential goods, mainly: pharmacies, grocery stores, drugstores, pet stores, opticians, newsagents, e-shop and Z찼silkovna pickup points, laundromats and drycleaners, towing services and carwashes, gas stations, gardening shops, florists, cellphone stores, computer and technical services, locksmiths, hardware stores, household goods, funeral homes, reverential goods, Christmas trees, decorations, branches, mistletoe, guns and ammunition.

The shops that are allowed to stay open will be open Monday to Saturday 5:00-22:59. On Sundays and public holidays, they must be CLOSED. Only gas stations, pharmacies, shops at airports and train stations and shops at medical facilities are allowed to be open on Sundays.

All shops that are not listed as exemptions have to be closed. Such as clothes and shoe shops, bookstores, jewelry shops, stationery shops, hobby markets, shops selling furniture and flooring and shops selling electronics.

If you go shopping, follow the hygienic rules (see Hygiene section). For the whole duration of shopping, it is necessary to wear amask and to keep social distance (especially when waiting in aqueue). Before entering the shop, disinfect your hands, and repeat after returning home. For more protection, shopping in gloves can be recommended. Don'ttouch any surfaces unnecessarily and use gloves when picking out fruit, vegetables or baked goods.

If you are part of ahigher risk group or are in quarantine (isolation), ask aneighbor, relative or friend to do your shopping. If this isn'tpossible, you can reach out to volunteers. Help and deliveries to high-risk groups and the infected), who will be happy to help. You can also order online and get your shopping delivered to your doorstep.

Shopping centers can only be entered in groups of 6people at most with avalid exception for families. The store must guarantee at least 15 m짼 of space per customer. In stores smaller than 15 m짼 this restriction does not apply to children under 15 and people with disabilities. In stores bigger than 15 m짼, children under 6with acompany of adult person are excluded.

Apriority entrance is ensured for persons with disabilities to prevent them from waiting in long queues. Store staff is not permitted to request usage of ashopping cart in case of individuals with baby-carriage, the baby in baby-carriage is exempt from limits on the number of customers allowed in the store.

The sales area, defined for the purposes of restricting the number of people, means the store area accessible to customers including changing rooms, area behind sales counters used by cashier/seller. Store offices and warehouses are not included. It is also mandatory to adopt regime and organisational measures and queue management (in front of and in the shop).

It is also mandatory to adopt regime and organisational measures and queue management (in front of and in the shop).

Try to shop online. If you enter ashop, follow all hygienic measures, social distance and pay by card. We have to shop but it is aplace where we encounter alot of people, so please, be responsible. You are protecting yourself and others.

5d.title: Halls of residence
5d.content:
Rules and recommendations

Due to the pandemic, it is now prohibited to provide accommodation in school educational and accommodation facilities to pupils and students who have their residence elsewhere in the Czech Republic. This also applies to university students.

There are exceptions to this. Pupils and students who are staying in dormitories and attend presence education can stay in youth homes and dormitories. Exceptions are also, for example, students participating in the practical training of medical and pedagogical disciplines or working students.

Ilive in adormitory

Pupils and students who have no other residence in the Czech Republic can stay in the dormitories. Aresidence is aplace where you intend to live permanently, aplace where you feel at home. If you prove by astatement that you feel at home in the dormitory and not elsewhere, you can continue to stay there.

If you stay on the dormitory, follow the increased hygienic measures (Wear Z: disinfect your hands face mask social distance).

However, the Ministry of Education is asking, if possible, for students and pupils to return to their home, in order to reduce their social contacts. Universities decide on the details of the operation of the dormitories independently. If you have any questions, please contact the dormitory operator directly.

If you are in danger of adifficult social situation in connection with this measure, contact your school as universities may award asocial scholarship to their students. Financial support is also offered by the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.

5e.title: Meeting friends
5e.content:
Rules and recommendations

Meetings are limited to 6people max. Keep the distance of at least 2meters with other people. According to the government regulations, contact with other people is strictly limited to the necessary occasions.

The current situation is very stressful for maintaining mental well-being. If you suffer from mental health problems, information from the Stress and Pandemic Impact Management might be useful for you.

Although, online platforms do not replace personal contact ameeting is not recommended. When ameeting is necessary, choose outdoor areas and wear aface mask.

You can find more about the meeting and relevant current measures in the section Meetings, parties, family celebrations.

5f.title: Distance learning
5f.content:
Rules and recommendations

For students who are not currently allowed apersonal presence in class, they are continuing remotely.

Participation in distance learning is compulsory for pupils. In the case of compulsory school attendance, the child must be excused within 3working days. When distance learning is in place follow the instructions you receive from teachers and the school. Especially at higher levels of education please follow the website and instructions given by the study department.

Distance learning depends on the possibility of remote connection. If you do not have the necessary equipment to complete this type of teaching, contact the school and ask for help. They should be ready to assist you in these types of situations, and if their supplies are limited, they will advise you to get help you need in adifferent place. For example, non-profit organizations can also help you with your difficulties.

At present we are dealing with anumber of new challenges, including distance learning. For both teachers and pupils and their parents, distance education is usually something new to them and they need time to adjust. Therefore, please be helpful and understand the needs of each other. We do not replace full-time teaching, but you can also learn alot online.

To successfully manage distance learning, we recommend setting up aschedule: Get up at aregular hour. Create aworkspace. Do not go to bed to connect to your lessons. Schedule your tasks and responsibilities. Make notes, it will help you keep attention. Communicate with teachers and classmates. Don'tbe afraid to ask at any time.

5g.title: How does tracing work?
5g.content:
The goal of tracing

The goal of tracing is to quickly identify potentially infected people, quarantine them, and protect the public.

Self-tracing

If you are infected with COVID-19, contact the people who you could have potentially infected.

Iwant to self-trace, but from when?

Iam asymptomatic: All epidemiologically significant contacts from 5days up to 1week before the date of receiving the COVID -19 positive PCR test.

Ihave symptoms of COVID -19: All epidemiologically significant contacts for 2days before the onset of the first symptoms until the date of receiving apositive PCR test.

Self-tracing form

After receiving the results of the positive test, you will also receive alink to the self-tracing formto your telephone number, where you can fill in the tracing data. Self-tracing forms are processed as apriority by the Regional Health Authority (KHS or Krajsk찼 hygienick찼 stanice in Czech).

Call from the Health Authority or tracing center

An employee of the health Authority or tracing center will call you and ask for your tracing information (prepare it in advance).

Prepare the following data for tracing:

  • name and surname of the contact
  • their telephone number
  • the day of the last contact with this person (if you are in the same household, the day of the last contact is the day of the positive PCR test).

Due to the amount of work, the hygiene station may contact you afew days after taking apositive test, so it is best to fill out aself-tracing form or call and inform your contacts yourself.

eRou큄ka

If you use the eRou큄ka application, you will receive an SMS code to your telephone number after the results of the positive test have been received. By entering the SMS code into the application, the people who the application has evaluated as your risky contacts will be automatically informed. The data is anonymous, so you don'thave to be afraid to insert it in eRou큄ka. Even one code can prevent dozens from getting infected.

5h.title: Divorced families
5h.content:
Rules and recommendations

The child has the right to have contact with both parents even during an emergency. Travel to transfer or take over children is one of the exceptions to restrictions on the movement of persons. An exception is also granted for necessary travel to family or close persons.

From alegal point of view, therefore, there is no reason not to comply with the court'sdecision concerning children.

On the other hand, it is necessary to consider all the risks and try to create rules that reduce the possibility of disease transmission. Especially if the risk of infection is higher for one of the parents (such as health professionals or other people who are in contact with the sick or more people). However, such adjustments to the regime should be based on the agreement of both parents.

We recommend maintaining contact with the child through telephone calls, video calls, and other tools that allow at least alternative contact if quarantine or other measures do not allow personal contact.

Achange in alternating care is also strongly recommended in case when one of the parents finds themself in isolation or quarantine. In this case, the transfer of the child should not take place. If the child is in the care of aparent who has to start quarantine for some reason, the child should remain in quarantine with that parent. If, on the other hand, the child is currently in the care of one parent and should transfer to aparent who has to start or is in quarantine as part of alternating care, we recommend that this transfer not take place.

5i.title: Visits in hospitals
5i.content:
Regulations

Visits of patients in the medical facilities of all medical service providers, offering inpatient care are prohibited.
The exception applies to visits of underage patients, patients with limited legal capacity, patients in hospice care, and patients in the terminal stage of incurable illnesses.

The presence of athird person during childbirth is allowed if the following conditions are met.

  • The third person is the second parent of the child or someone who lives in the same household as the mother
  • The birth will take place in aprivate room or birthing area
  • The visitor can'tcome into contact with any of the other future mothers
  • The visitor'stemperature will be measured before entering the room or designated birthing area
  • The visitor'stemperature does not reach 37째C and they don'thave any symptoms of the coronavirus
  • The visitor hasto wear at least asurgical face mask the whole time (afabric face mask, non-surgical face mask, or scarf will not suffice).

Please check other rules and measures of individual providers of healthcare.

5j.title: Work-agreements and self-employed
5j.content:
Recommendation

If you have lost income or lost part of it as aresult of the coronavirus crisis, use one of the state compensation options. Apply for compensation if you are self-employed (OSV) or employed on DPP / DP. This is abonus of 500 crowns for each day when the establishment was closed, or your business was prevented or restricted. You can find more detailed conditions for obtaining compensation in the Compensation bonus section.

If you do business inthe affected sector of culture, you, unfortunately, cannot apply for compensation.

If you are renting an establishment that you have had to close as aresult of government regulations, see also COVID -Rent II section.

The Ministry also allows for the deferral of tax obligations. You can find more about deferrals in theLarge Tax LiberationPackage section.

5k.title: Non-emergency care
5k.content:
Recommendations

Contact your hospital or polyclinic and get the information on the provision of non-emergency care.

Do not, however, postpone preventative checkups.

5l.title: Hygiene recommendations for children and students
5l.content:
Recommendation

To best prevent the spread of coronavirus, it is important to follow the rule: Face mask, hand sanitation, social distance.

Wearing aface mask (over your mouth and nose) is one of the most effective prevention against coronavirus infection. Aface mask is effective only if it covers the entire area of the nose and mouth. The face mask must be worn indoors, but also in villages and towns. Learn how to handle aface mask safely in the Face maskssection.

Another important prevention is frequent and thorough hand washingand the use of disinfection. In this way, you can prevent the infection from getting into your body (mostly mouth, nose, and eyes) from your hands, from where the virus can then spread to your body.

It is also important to keep agap in aplace with ahigher concentration of people. The recommended distance you should keep is 2meters.

All these methods of prevention protect not only you but also your loved ones, parents, grandparents, and other people who could fall into the risk category for whom the coronavirus is particularly dangerous.

5m.title: Playgrounds
5m.content:
Rules and recommendations

Public playgrounds are open. However, it is important to follow all government regulations in their area to prevent the transmission of the disease to your home and loved ones.

Currently, it is necessary to wear aface mask when in avillage or town. This also applies to playgrounds.

Also, keep adistance of 2meters from other people and do not associate. Try to make sure that children behave within the framework of these recommendations.

Do not enter the field of play if it is already so busy that it would not be possible to keep distances from other people. In this case, consider the security of the area and the risk of infection.

Try to limit the length of your stay on the field so that people do not accumulate in the place, but rather take turns.

We recommend that both child and you thoroughly disinfect their hands after visiting the playground.

5n.title: Visits to social facilities
5n.content:
Regulation

Visits toany social service providers' facilities,retirement homes, homes with special arrangements, and any respite care, social services in the residential form are prohibited.

The exception tothe ban applies to:

  • Underage occupants of social service care
  • Occupants with limited legal capacity
  • Occupants with disabilities occupants whose psychological state or social situation requires it
  • Occupants, in the terminal stage of an incurable illness.

5o.title: Children'scontact with their friends
5o.content:
Rules and recommendations

Meetings are limited to 6people max. Keep the distance of at least 2meters with other people. According to the government regulations, contact with other people is strictly limited to the necessary occasions.

Although, online platforms do not replace personal contact ameeting is not recommended. When ameeting is necessary, choose outdoor areas and wear aface mask. You can find out more about meetings and relevant current measures in the section Meetings, parties, family celebrations.

Try to meet with your friends online. Help your kids to organise aphone call, play an online game together, or have atext conversation with their friends.

The current situation represents ahuge strain on the mental health of all of us. Children perceive this stress very strongly as well as adults. Especially, if they are separated from their friends, grandparents and detached from the school or other environment. If your child is suffering from mental health problems due to the isolation, fear of illness or stress from current state, we recommend reviewing the Stress and Pandemic Impact Management.

5p.title: Divorced families
5p.content:
Rules and recommendations

The child has the right to have contact with both parents even during the State of an emergency. Travel for the purpose of transferring or taking over children is one of the exceptions to restrictions on the free movement of people. An exception is also granted for the purpose of necessary travel to family or close ones.

From alegal point of view, therefore, there is no reason not to comply with the court'sdecision concerning children.

On the other hand, it is necessary to consider all the risks and try to create rules that reduce the possibility of disease transmission. Especially if the risk of infection is higher for one of the parents (such as health professionals or other people who are in contact with sick or generally more people). However, such adjustments to the regime should be based on the agreement of both parents.

Achange in alternating care is also strongly recommended in the event that one of the parents finds himself in isolation or quarantine. In this case, the transfer of the child should not take place. If the child is in the care of aparent who has to start quarantine for some reason, the child should remain in quarantine with that parent. If, on the other hand, the child is currently in the care of one parent and should transfer to aparent who has to start or is in quarantine as part of alternating care, we recommend that this transfer not take place.

5q.title: Dealing with official matters
5q.content:
Rules and recommendations

Office hours are limited to 2days aweek for 5hours. You can find the opening hours for each Office on the official board of the given office, which is placed by the office building entrance.

Written and/or telephone contact is preferable over apersonal visit to the office. This will help reduce the risk of infection to you and those around you.

You can also set up adata-box free of charge for online communication with the authorities. The data-box can be set up at any CzechPoint branch. If you have an e-ID (eObanka), you can set up adata box online.

Only necessary matters should be handled in person. If you go to the office in person, it is necessary to have afacemask at all times, disinfect your hands and keep your distance. Keep adistance not only when in the queue but also when communicating with the officials.

If you need to stay at home with your child, fill out the application form for nursing. If you need more information about compensation within the nursing home, you can find it inCaregiver'sallowance for self-employed IIor Caregiver'sallowance for full-time employees section.

If you are the recipient of housing allowance, child allowance or you have an increased care allowance of CZK 2,000, an extraordinary measure applies to you. Therefore, you do not have to document anything and submit to the Labor Office of the Czech Republic income or paid costs for housing for the months of July, August, September. You will receive the same amount automatically for the months of October, November, and December.

5r.title: Child'sillness
5r.content:
Recommendation

If your child develops Covide-19 symptoms, contact your pediatrician.

In most cases, children are asymptomatic or have avery mild course of the disease. Your child'sgeneral practitioner will advise you on how to alleviate any symptoms of coronavirus.

Make sure the baby rests and drinks plenty of fluids. Continue the rest of the treatment and alleviate the symptoms as instructed by your doctor.

One of the first symptoms in children may be the so-called "covid fingers", which are red and swollen. Read more here.

Wait for the instructions of the Regional Hygiene Station and continue according to its instructions.

If amember of the household, in this case, achild, is quarantined, others need to be isolated. More information on this situation can be found in the Ahousehold member is positive section.

If your situation allows, place the child who has been infected in aseparate room. This will reduce the risk of the disease spreading to your home.

  • Treat the infected person with mouth and nose protection.
  • Wash your hands and laundry often.
  • Contact limit.
  • Dine in aseparate area.
  • Try not to use the same objects.
  • Monitor your health.

5s.title: Child birth
5s.content:
Rules and recommendations

The birth of achild is always ajoyful occasion. However, it is important to follow strict hygiene rules. This way you will prevent the infection from spreading to the hospital environment. It is crucial to protect not just patients, but also the medical staff.

The participation of athird party in childbirth is permitted if the conditions are met:

  • The third party is the child'ssecond parent or aperson living with the mother in the same household.
  • The birth will take place in aseparate delivery room or delivery area with its own bathroom.
  • Contact of the third party with other mothers will be prevented.
  • The third person undergoes temperature measurement before entering the delivery room or delivery area.
  • The third person has abody temperature of less than 37.0째 Cand at the same time has no COVID-19 symptoms.
  • The third party uses asurgical face mask as minimum respiratory protection (Non-surgical and fabric drapes or scarves are not enough !!)

We understand thatfor mothers, childbirth is very stressful and the presence of aclose person can be helpful. However, this is possible under strict restrictions only.If you still suffer from stress, anxiety, or any psychological problems, you can read the Stress and handling impacts of the pandemic section.

5t.title: Sporting events
5t.content:
Rules and recommendations

Sporting events are not generally allowed, but it is now possible to request an exception from the National Sports Agency (NSA). The organizers of these events must submit aplan to the NSA to meet strict hygiene conditions, which will then be evaluated by the NSA together with the chief hygienist.

The primary condition is the mandatory testing of players before each event. Other requirements include having the minimum number of people in the organizing team and the minimum number of journalists for the event. The conditions will be assessed individually for each specific event. Fan participation is prohibited. Authorized persons will have to follow general hygiene rules (face masks, social distancing).

Exceptions for organizing competitions have already been granted to the professional volleyball league (men from November 14th 2020, women fromNovember 21st 2020) and aprofessional basketball league (from November 13th2020). Fan participation is prohibited.

Professional athletes are allowed to have training in order to prepare for future events both at indoor and outdoor sports grounds in unlimited numbers. However, they are required to observe all applicable hygienic measures - keep the distance and disinfect hands. Athletes do not have to wear face masks during the sport itself, but after training, it is necessary to put on the face mask again in accordance with the regulations.

Aprofessional athlete is aperson who performs sport as his or her primary job or as abusiness and other similar activity.

5u.title: Castles and palaces
5u.content:
Rules and recommendations

Visits and tours of castles and palaces are banned.

5v.title: Zoos and botanical gardens
5v.content:
Rules and recommendations

Visits and tours in zoos and botanical gardens are banned.

5w.title: Other sports
5w.content:
Rules and recommendations

Amateur sports

Outdoor gyms, sports centres, and sports grounds are open to the public and amateur sports. Due to the free movement of people ban however, any amateur sports are limited to 6people only. Outdoor gyms remain open, you do not need to wear aface mask while exercising. Please maintain increased hygiene measures, especially social distancing, and regular hand hygiene.

Running and other individual sports

Jogging is allowed in the park or in nature (also on the way to the park/nature). The obligation to wear aface mask does not apply to sports, however, we recommend wearing your face mask even while exercising. Similar rules apply to other individual sports (e.g.playing golf in nature is allowed).

Professional sports

Professional athletes are exempted from the free movement of people ban. Aprofessional athlete is aperson who performs aparticular sports activity as his or her primary job, as abusiness, or asimilar activity. Professional athletes can do/play sports in order to prepare for any future sports events. They can use both, indoor and outdoor sports grounds, in this case, the number of people is not limited. Professional athletes however are still required to observe all hygienic measures the social distancing and hand sanitizing. Athletes do not have to wear face masks while training. After any training, however, according to current regulations, it is necessary for the professional athletes to wear their face masks again.

5x.title: SMS with afake positive result
5x.content:
SMS with afake positive result

Hoax

Afriend of afriend went to get tested with her daughter. They registered, but because there were too many people, they left after three hours and went home. Afew days later, they both received an SMS, telling them they are positive.

Explanation

This hoax has been appearing since spring of 2020 in different versions across the whole world. There are allegedly tens of people who know someone who went through something similar. None of the people who this allegedly happened to have ever been able to show any proof like an SMS with the test number or the name of alaboratory. If you ask them for proof, they usually retract their claim about apositive test.

This story is not plausible from alogical standpoint for anumber of reasons: If you have an electrical request form, you don'thave to wait for your test for hours, the waiting time is usually max 1hour. The registration, explanation of the process and assignment of aspecific person to aspecific test happens right before the test (after having waited in the queue). Until that point, you are only registered in the system of online request forms because no one can tell which testing site you will choose to visit. The only option for afalse SMS to be sent is if the wrong personal identification number or the wrong phone number were entered. This, however, is not an error in the system.

An explanation of the whole hoax (in Czech). Asimilar case being shared in Slovakia.

The probability of afalse PCR test result

Hoax

This hoax also comes from avideo from lawyer Reiner Fuellmich, where he claims that the possibility of receiving afalse positive test is between 89-94%, so almost certain.

Explanation

According to astudy by Oxford university the accuracy of PCR tests is between 95-99%. Other studies prove the same thing. The results of many other available PCR test studies show that don쨈treact to any other viruses, including other coronaviruses.

An explanation of the whole hoax (in Czech).

Oxford university study.

Other studyand another one.

Automatic positive test

Hoax

If you don'tarrive at atest after having been in contact with someone who is Covid-19 positive, you are automatically seen as positive as well.

Explanation

If you are ordered to go get tested and placed in quarantine after having met someone positive, you have two obligations. Two arrive at the test and to follow all the rules for being in quarantine. If you do not arrive at the test, you can be fined but on no account will you be seen as positive. The result can only be determined as aresult of atest. If all the samples can'tbe done in one day, they are tested the next day. This can be seen in the number of positive tests in aday, when Mondays in general have the lowest numbers, because less tests are carried out during the weekend and so it isn'tnecessary to run tests from previous days.

Explanation of the whole hoax (in Czech).Another explanation(in Czech).

5y.title: Non Covid-related deaths blamed on Covid-19
5y.content:
Hoax:

Three days ago, my colleagues father-in-law passed away from aheart attack. The autopsy report stated that he died of the coronavirus. When my colleague and his wife wanted an explanation, they got to the director of the hospital who confessed after an argument that they have orders to do so and they get higher rewards for Covid deaths. This is not alie, it actually happened to my colleague. This happens with most deaths. They lie to us, scare us and manipulate us.

Explanation:

This hoax has been appearing in different versions since the so-called first wave. Sometimes the hospitals are forced to fake the death reports because of an order from above and sometimes they offer afinancial reward to the families of the deceased if they agree to state Covid-19 as the cause of death and sometimes it'sthe funeral services who ask for Covid-19 being stated as the cause of death, as they allegedly get ahigher reward.

There is one thing all of these hoaxes have in common and that'sthe lack of: the place where it happened, the name of the hospital or the name of the funeral home. The story always happens to arelative of someone they know. These people never respond to any requests for proof and only refer to their previous statements. The important thing is, there is no such thing as Covid-19 being stated as the cause of death.

Medical reports only state whether the person was tested for the presence of the SARS-CoV-19 coronavirus, which causes the illness Covid-19. Therefore it doesn'tmake sense for only Covid-19 being stated as the cause of death.

5z.title: Penalties
5z.content:
Wearing aface mask

The extraordinary measures issued by the Ministry of Health the state obligation to wear aface mask. Afine of up to CZK 10,000 can be imposed on the spot for violating these measures. Afine can be imposed on the spot or the matter can be referred to administrative proceedings. You can find the rules on face masks in the Face mask section.

The penalties are governed by this legislation

Penaltiesresult from Act No. 258/2000 Sb., on the protection of public health (짠 92n (1) (b) of this Act) and Act No. 250/2016 Sb. on the liability for offences and proceedings concerning them (짠 91 of this Act).

Violation of the governmental crisis measures

Most of the current restrictions fall under the crisis measures of the government and violating them could lead to afine of up to CZK 20,000.

The penalties are governed by this legislation

Penalties result from Act No. 240/2000 Sb., on Crisis Management and on Amendments to Certain Acts (Crisis Act) (짠 34 (1) (a) of this Act)

Violation of work duty

Failure to perform the imposed work duty can result in afine of up to CZK 50,000.

The penalties are governed by this legislation

Penalties result from Act No. 240/2000 Coll., on Crisis Management and on Amendments to Certain Acts (Crisis Act) (짠 34 (1) (b) of this Act).

6a.title: Myths about COVID-19
6a.content:
Covid does not exist

Hoax:

This hoax appears in hundreds of forms. Its purpose is to convince the reader that there is in fact no pandemic and that everything is just a"clever" form of deception to gain control of humanity.

Explanation:

Apandemic is amass occurrence of an infectious disease across many different regions. The WHO declared SARS-CoV-2 apandemic on 11.32020. Up until 3.11. almost 47 million people had been infected worldwide and 1.21 million people had passed away as aresult of the infection. All arguments about the inexistence of apandemic are completely false.

5G networks spread the coronavirus

Hoax:

"The coronavirus and its spread is related to 5G networks."

Explanation:

SARS-CoV-2 is avirus that is transmitted through respiratory droplets by coughing, sneezing or contact with acontaminated surface. In no case is its spread possible by radio waves. Likewise, there is no scientific evidence to demonstrate any effect of electronic signals on the human immune system or DNA structure.

The WHO has stated that Covid is not dangerous

Hoax:

This hoax gained traction after an interview in the discussion program Prima Partie, where Lenka Zl찼malov찼 said: The World Health Organization (WHO) has currently published acompletely new study, which we could call ameta-analysis that brings together data from about seventy studies from around the world, which show that the danger of the virus and the mortality of the virus are both many times lower than previously stated. The original figures were 3.4%, while the latest ones mentioned were between 1% and 0.4%. Now the WHO, which still has some authority, says it's0.23%. To give viewers an idea, this is at the level not of the flu, but common viruses. So Iwonder how the government and the new the health minister will react to this. Because if we find that this is the current situation, then the strict measures are completely inadequate. "

Explanation:

This false statement was subsequently spread mainly in disinformation groups on social networks.

You can find an explanation of this hoax here.

6b.title: Myths about eRou큄ka app
6b.content:
The eRou큄ka app is being used to monitor the population

Hoax: Different variations of the statement: eRou큄ka is being used to watch people.

Explanation: The eRou큄ka app does not collect and save GPS data, but the Android operating system does include some Bluetooth LE (low energy) services that eRou큄ka needs to function within location services- specifically Google Play Services. This is why the user needs to agree to the app having access to certain location data. This is not necessary for users with the iOS operating system. Why the location services need to be on is explained by google here (in Czech).

For the app to work, you only need to turn on Bluetooth( for both iOS and Android).

6c.title: Impossibility to repay aloan or amortgage - business
6c.content:
Rules and recommendations

The COVID-19 pandemic has amajor impact on the domestic economy. Many people are unable to repay their loans or mortgages due to aloss of income. One of the possible solutions was to apply for aso-called instalment moratorium in the last six months, i.e.apostponement of instalments. The moratorium ended on October 31st - if you can no longer repay your loans or mortgages, you do not have to worry.

There are solutions to your financial problems. The first step should be to contact your creditor as soon as possible. Do not wait for anything and contact your bank or non-banking company by phone or via the Internet. Currently, banks provide individual solutions for your specific case. Most banks have clear instructions on their websites to help explain your problem. If the bank refuse, you always have the option of having your application checked by the bank'sombudsman, who will find out whether the bank has complied with the regulations.

Clients of non-banking companies have aright to contact Czech Leasing and Financial Association or Association of Non-banking Credit Providers. If your financial difficulties persist, contact the Financial Distress Counseling Center or the Financial Arbiter.

6d.title: Working with aclient
6d.content:
Rules and recommendations

The provision of services in establishments is currently prohibited. Although, individual work for the client is allowed, due to the seriousness of the current epidemiological situation, we do not recommend working with clients. Please check in advance that your client does not have symptoms of COVID-19. If so, do not meet them in person. If you do not feel well or have symptoms, do not visit the client under any circumstances.

If you go home to the client, follow all hygienic rules. Wash your hands after entering the household and wear aface mask - ask your client to wear aface mask as well. If possible, keep the recommended distance. If you touch the client during work (hairdresser, massage), we recommend using disposable gloves.

If you are carrying out an activity in which there is an increased spread of droplets (teaching wind instruments, teaching singing, etc.), reconsider your visit. After work, disinfect your work tools that may be contaminated (hairdressing scissors, musical instruments, etc.).

6e.title: Spiritual activities
6e.content:
Rules and recommendations

Spiritual activities can help people in this mentally challenging time. Churches and various religious groups are trying to find away to continue their activities safely.

Services and religious gatherings

Services and similar religious gatheringsare allowed but only 20people can be present. The general obligationto wear amaskapplies.

It is obligatory to keep a2-meter distance from others,people living in the same household are exempt from this rule. Upon entering abuildingyou must disinfect your hands.

The rule of amaximum of 5people singing together indoors applies.

Individual spiritual service is also allowed, ie services, ceremonies and spiritual accompaniments, in which, in addition to the clergy onlyone family which shares ahousehold participates.

Most churches offer virtual services that you can watch over the Internet or television.

Amaximum of 20people can take part in the preparation of the virtual service. But only 5people can sing together.

Individual prayer

Individual visits to churches for prayer are allowed, but the situation varies from church to church. Most parishes have established websites where you can find out under what conditions you can visit the church. The same goes for synagogues and mosques.

It is obligatory to wear aface mask inside- also observe hygienic measures (do not touch your face, wash your hands etc.).

Individual spiritual care and services

As for confessions, most churches carry them out after individual arrangements, so we recommend following your parish'swebsite for more information.

Priests can continue to provide individual services - they are even exempted from the curfew if they are called, for example, for the last anointing.

6f.title: Shopping
6f.content:
Pravidla adoporuen챠

Shop for more days in advance.

Choose atime to shop when there are fewer people in the store. Only be in the shop for the necessary time.

When entering and leaving the store, disinfect your hands with the antibacterial gel located by the entrance.

When going to astore please note that the number of customers in astore at one time is restricted. The maximum customer density allowed is 1customer per 15 sq mvending area. This restriction, however, does not apply to aperson accompanying aholder of an ID card for severely disabled (TP/ZTP, ZTP/P).

Ask relatives or neighbours if they would help you buy groceries. It is also possible to use the services of volunteers.

6g.title: Protection from the virus
6g.content:
Recommendation

The most important rule is often mentioned - wear aface mask, wash your hands and keep the distance from others.Together with aminimum of social contacts, this rule is simple and very effective prevention against the COVID-19 disease.

Do not go to places with ahigher concentration of people unless it is necessary. There are volunteer groups that can bring your groceries right to your home. If you are planning to visit family, choose awalk together instead of staying in aclosed room.

6h.title: Mental support for the elderly
6h.content:
Recommendation

The current situation is especially confusing and stressful for seniors. The general advice is to go outside as little as possible - go out only for the most necessary purchases or to the doctor, always with aface mask on. It is better to skip visiting relatives for awhile. Although it'snot easy, try to keep in touch with your children, grandchildren and other relatives or friends, by phone. Try to ask someone from your area to pick-up groceries, medicine at the pharmacy, or even walking the dog.

Here are some basic tips on how to handle apandemic:

  • If you feel nervous, upset, or confused, that'sfine. These feelings are acompletely natural reaction to anew, unknown situation.
  • Talk about your feelings - call your children, grandchildren, or friends.
  • If you feel that your feelings are difficult to manage, contact one of the helplines, their trained staff will advise you on what to do in difficult situations. Crisis lines are also available for regular conversations. You can find alist of them below.
  • Don'tbe afraid to ask for help if you need it. Seniors are one of the most vulnerable groups, so it is only natural that they need help. Trained volunteers can help with picking-up groceries, medicine, or even walking your dog. Volunteers are provided by some municipal offices.
  • Do not underestimate the situation, but try to avoid panic. Limit the time you spend reading the newspaper and watching the news. You can do better for yourself if you read abook, solve acrossword puzzle, or watch your favorite movie.
  • Try to follow aproper lifestyle - try to sleep enough, eat quality food, keep your mind busy by reading and other activities - ideas can be found in the brochure How to Survive Quarantine and Stay Active on Body and Spirit? You can find more ideas for activities in the brochure (in Czech) published by the Association of Clinical Psychologists of the Czech Republic

For general advice on how to maintain mental well-being, seePandemic Stress and Impacts> Mental Hygiene

Where to go for advice, specific help, or if you want to break with someone?

  • Senior phone (Life 90): 800 157 157 (nonstop), FREE
  • Senior line (Elpida): 800 200 007 (daily 8-20), FREE, the line also provides assistance to seniors in cooperation with the Scouts
  • Line for seniors (Senior with pleasure): 792 308 798 (nonstop)
  • Green line (Andl Str찼탑n첵): 800 603 030 (nonstop), FREE
  • Helpline for the elderly and those in need: 800 160 166, non-stop, FREE

6i.title: Services
6i.content:
Rules and recommendations

Providing services is not allowed now.

Only certain services are allowed to operate, specifically: car repair shops and towing service, deliveries and messengers, electronics and home appliances repair shops, locksmiths, financial advisors,building and demolishing companies, and saloons for cats and dogs.

Any kind of service which is not on the list of exceptions is not allowed to operate. Exceptions do not cover for example barber shops, hairdressers, manicure and pedicure, massages, beauticians, etc. Though, it is possible to make an appointment at your home as the prohibition applies only to providing aservice at the place of business. With respect to the risk of infection being still high, we highly recommend making an appointment only when truly necessary.

Once meeting with the service provider is set, please follow hygienic rules during the meeting wear your face mask, keep spacing and disinfect your hands regularly.

You can visit the store/shopping mall in agroup of 6people at most with avalid exception for families. The store must guarantee at least 15 m짼 of space per customer. In stores smaller than 15 m짼 this restriction does not apply to children under 15 and people with disabilities. In stores bigger than 15 m짼, children under 6with acompany of adult person are excluded.

Apriority entrance is ensured for persons with disability to prevent them from waiting in long queues.

It is also mandatory to adopt regime and organizational measures and queue management (in front of and in the shop).

Minor repairs in the household and hairdresser visit should be postponed in these days. Please use service providers only in cases of necessity. If so, please pay increased attention to hygiene keep spacing and use contactless payment. Please be careful and responsible. By respecting these rules, you help us to protect you and other people.

6j.title: Journeys to tests or doctor
6j.content:
Recommendations

Call your doctor firstand consult with them, if it is necessary for you to come in person. If you need to see adoctor in person. Try to avoid places with an increased risk of infection.

If possible, travel by car or call ataxi. Only stay in the waiting room for the necessary time and keep the distances between other patients.

Of course, cover your mouth and nose with aface mask. Avoid touching objects that have been touched by patients before you (such as handles, railings).

However, do not underestimate the importance of preventive health checkups!

6k.title: Keeping in touch with family
6k.content:
Recommendation

Personal contact with family members is allowed. But consider whether the visit is necessary and urgent and whether acallwould be sufficient.

If aface-to-face meeting is urgent, it will be safer if you are visited by arelative who works from home and does not associate with strangers, or with people who recently suffered from COVID-19, and successfully recovered, and were released from isolation. An outdoor place is asuitable for such ameeting.

6l.title: Banks and insurance
6l.content:
Rules and recommendations

Banks and insurance companies are open.

Written or phone communication is preferred. You can also sort out many things online. It is good to use e.g.internet banking.

Only sort out undelayable matters in person. Before visiting the bank or insurance company in person, it is good to call ahead and verify, whether the matter cant be sorted out via telephone or over the internet or schedule atime for your visit.

While in the bank or insurance company, wear amask and social distance. Before entering, disinfect your hands. If you know that you will have to sign adocument, it is good to bring your own pen, so you don'thave to unnecessarily touch surfaces after other people.

If it'spossible, opt for contactless payment (transfer, card...) rather than cash. Alarge number of people touch money and not doing so when possible can decrease the risk of infection.

6m.title: Dealing with official matters
6m.content:
Recommendation

Handle only urgent matters. Follow the rules of wearing aface mask, hand sanitization, and distancing. You can only benefit from wearing gloves as well.

6n.title: Health resorts
6n.content:
Rules and recommendations

It is only possible to offer rehabilitation and spa carein case of health care recommended therapy.

If receiving aspa treatment, follow the hygienic measures and wear amask in common areas. If you have any signs of arespiratory illness (acough or breathing problems) or atemperature before your stay, consult your doctor whether to get tested or postpone your stay. If you meet someone positive, get tested before you arrive at the spa.

Medical care and other illnesses cannot be neglected as aresult of Covid-19. If prescribed by adoctor, and you are without any signs of the coronavirus, you can visit aspa. The more considerate you are towards employees and other guests, such as following all hygienic measures, the more pleasant and safe your stay will be.

Visitations are not allowed.

6o.title: Exercise
6o.content:
Recommendation

Especially during apandemic, try to follow aproper lifestyle - get enough sleep, eat quality whole foods, keep your mind busy by reading and other activities - ideas for activities for your body and mind can be found in the brochure (in Czech)How to Survive Quarantine and Stay Active on Body and Spirit? published by the Association of Clinical Psychologists of the Czech Republic.

But keep in mind that the gyms are now closed.

6p.title: How to treat information
6p.content:
Recommendation

Track news from trusted sources.

How to know that asource of information is trustworthy?

  • Check the information from another source
  • The author of the texts is not anonymous
  • The text should not be emotionally influenced by the author
  • Know if it is an objective report or asubjective opinion

Find out more in section Hoaxes.

6q.title: Shopping malls
6q.content:
Rules and recommendations

Only shops selling essential goods (especially groceries, pharmacies, and chemistsshop) are allowed to open in the shopping malls. Other shops remain closed. Catering facilities together with takeout points cannot be opened in shopping centres with asales area exceeding 5,000 m짼. There is an exception for delivery services to pick up ameal from restaurants located in shopping malls.

You can visit ashopping mall in agroup of 6people at most with avalid exception for families. The store must guarantee at least 15 m짼 of space per customer. In stores smaller than 15 m짼 this restriction does not apply to children under 15 and people with disabilities. In stores bigger than 15 m짼, children under 6with acompany of adult person are excluded.

Apriority entrance is ensured for persons with disability to prevent them from waiting in long queues. Store staff is not permitted to request usage of ashopping cart in case of individuals with baby-carriage, the baby in baby-carriage is exempt from limits on the number of allowed people in the store.

The sales area, defined for the purposes of restricting the number of people, means the store area accessible to customers including changing rooms, the area behind sales counters used by cashier/seller. Store offices and warehouses are not included. It is also mandatory to adopt regime and organizational measures and queue management (in front of and in the shop).

Wi-fi in the shopping malls are currently unavailable; likewise, it is not possible to use relax zones within the mall (benches, armchairs, etc.).

FAQ related to this topic is available here.

6r.title: Wholesale
6r.content:
Rules and recommendations

Wholesale is mainly intended for business owners shopping in relation to their business.

Sole traders and companies must prove their business ownership. This can be done by showing acopy of their trade license (in most shops aphoto on your phone should suffice). You can also prove your business by telling the store your IO (company identification number), which the shop can verify in the state database. One IO can be used to admit one person.

Merchandise pickup points and delivery are allowed to function and goods from the suppliers are allowed to be brought in.

When shopping, follow all hygienic rules, wear your mask the whole time and disinfect your hands before entering. Enter the shops only when necessary to ensure the safety of yourself and the employees, where possible, choose to order online and use apickup or delivery service.

6s.title: Repair shops and after-sale services
6s.content:
Rules and recommendation

In general, retail sale and the provision of service are not allowed, there are, however, certain exceptions which include some repair and service shops.

Car and bicycle services are allowed to be open. Other services allowed to be open are electronics and household appliance services and repairs. Car washes are also allowed to stay open.

Other repairs and services that havent been mentioned in the exceptions have to be closed.

Information on the hygienic rules that have to be followed when visiting aservice or repair shop can be found in the Hygiene section.

6t.title: CURRENT: Slavic carnival, slaughter feast
6t.content:
Rules and recommendations

Carnival celebrations and pig-slaughters belong to the traditional events in our country. Unfortunately, in the current situation, it is not possible to organize these events due to the free movement of people ban.

To reduce the risk of the infection, pig-slaughters can only be organized within the family circle. When handling raw meats, we recommend wearing disposable gloves and wearing aface mask while cooking. Before you distribute any meat products to your friends, please do not forget to put your face mask on and to wash your hands.

6u.title: Delivery and courier services
6u.content:
Rules and recommendation

Package delivery and courier services are allowed to operate.

You can order packages online or by phone and have them delivered to your home. You can also have food or your shopping delivered.

Package pickup points (e.g.Z찼silkovna) are allowed to operate as well as online store pickup points. Shops can deliver their products without enlisting the services of another company by having apickup window.

Online shopping should be preferred over physically entering ashop. Enlisting package delivery and courier services is the easiest way to get your shopping done while the shops are closed. When receiving apackage, make sure to follow the hygienic rules. It is good to pay in advance (by transfer), or if paying when receiving the package to pay by card. If possible, unpack the ordered goods outside your living area (e.g.in agarden or in your hallway).

When receiving apackage, make sure to wear amask for the whole time and disinfect your hands before and after. If you follow all of these rules, you can buy everything you need and at asignificantly lower risk than in ashop. Please be considerate and protect yourself and others.

6v.title: Driver'seducation
6v.content:
Rules and recommendations

Based on the protective measure adopted by the Czech Government, theoperation of driving schools is prohibited. This also applies to exams of professional competence and similar activities defined by the Act on the acquisition and improvement of professional competence to drive motor vehicles.

At the moment, it is possible to take both parts of the final exam in the usual way.

You can train the theoretical part of the exam online from the comfort of your home.

6w.title: E-shop
6w.content:
Rules and recommendations

Pickup points and delivery services for online stores are allowed to operate. Shops are allowed to distribute products ordered online in advance without enlisting the services of another company by establishing their own pickup window.

Online shopping should be preferred over going into shops. Ordering online is agreat way to get your shopping done while the stores are closed. When receiving apackage it is important to follow all hygienic rules. It is good to pay in advance (by transfer) or to pay by card if you pay while receiving your package. If possible, unpack the ordered goods outside your living area (e.g.in agarden or in your hallway).

When receiving merchandise bought online at apickup point or at home, wear your mask and disinfect your hands before. If you follow all of these rules, you can buy everything you need and at asignificantly lower risk than in ashop. Please be considerate and protect yourself and others.

During the state of emergency all consumer rights are protected. You have the right to return or reclaim any merchandise bought online. However, we recommend only sorting out undelayable matters and leaving the rest for when shops start operating as usual again. The most important thing is to protect your health and the health of others, to follow all hygienic rules and not to expose yourself to unnecessary contact with those outside your inner circle.

6x.title: Dangerous vaccines and foreign soldiers in the Czech Republic
6x.content:
Dangerous vaccines and testing

Hoax:

Excerpt: "According to Prymula, the first batch of the vaccine could be finished at the end of this year. The fact that he has agreat interest in vaccinating the Czech population is also shown by Prymula'sstatement from October 8th for the Novinky.cz server: 'Vaccinated people will not have to wear face masks and will have anumber of other bonuses, so Ithink the interest in vaccination will be quite high. "According to the director of Novavax Erck and the Prime Minister Babi큄, in return for producing the vaccine in the Czech republic and enabling aclinical study on our population, the Czech republic will receive the vaccine as apriority."

Explanation:

Conspiracy theories about forced or widespread vaccination in relation to the coronavirus are very often associated with disinformation narratives about "secret elite intentions and vaccination as ameans of establishing totalitarian world domination. "It mainly benefits from the irrational belief of some people that vaccines are not only ineffective but even dangerous. Such (dis) information is currently pointless and its main purpose is to provoke fear, distrust, and panic.

The vaccine must undergo several clinical trials before being placed on the market to rule out any unwanted effects and the presence of unwanted substances. Only after their removal and the successful completion of all tests is it possible to release the vaccine to the market.

Vaccines in the Czech Republic will only be tested on volunteers who will be under observation and paid for the testing. This is common practice in the clinical trials of all vaccines.

Foreign soldiers in the Czech Republic

Hoax:

"Under the pretext of the coronavirus, the US is moving huge numbers of soldiers, planes and tanks to Europe. We are on the brink of war, says the expert. The United States has never occupied Europe with such astrong army as it is doing now. The presence of American doctors in the Czech republic is apreparation for the invasion of American troops into the Czech republic."

Explanation:

In fact, it is aNATO exercise that was announced in advance.

The Czech government has agreed to the stay of military medics of NATO and EU member states for up to 300 people for aperiod of 90 days, in order to manage the Covid-19 pandemic.

In addition, former Minister of Health Roman Prymula said that ateam of 28 National Guard doctors from the US states of Nebraska and Texas would arrive in the Czech Republic. According to the Minister of Defense Lubom챠r Metnar, this is purely medical aid, so they will serve without weapons and under the supervision of Czech medics. The stay of all soldiers first must be approved by both chambers of Parliament.

6y.title: Markets, farmers markets
6y.content:
Rules and recommendations

Market stalls, markets and farmers' markets are prohibited. The only exceptions are markets and stalls with selected products. Specifically, only fresh or processed fruits, vegetables, milk and dairy products, meat and meat products, eggs, bakery and confectionery products, honey and honey products can be sold on the markets, and only if they are produced in the Czech Republic.

The ban on the sale of products in stalls does not apply to mobile markets (selling drugs) and food trucks also does not apply in places where it is not possible to buy goods in another store (typically in smaller villages without shops).

If this exemption is applied and the markets take place, increased hygiene measures must be observed. Consumption of food and drink is also prohibited where markets take place. There can be 1person on the market for 15m ^ 2at atime and without distance of 2m agroup of max. 6people will be possible. With the exception of members of the common household. Stalls, tables or other sales areas must be located min. 4meters apart.

Although markets take place outside, there is alarge concentration of people in asmall space, so it was necessary to temporarily reduce this form of sale in order to slow down the spread of the disease. Nevertheless, there are certain exceptions to the general ban - it is possible to sell local products from Czech farmers. If you go to the markets, keep your safe distance and wear aface mask at all times. If you buy some food or drinks, take them and consume them ideally at home.

All other forms of stall and market sales are prohibited.

6z.title: St. Nicholas Day
6z.content:
Recommendations

St. Nicholas, Angel and the Devil walk on the 5th of December every year. This tradition is very popular amongst parents and their children, at least amongst the naughty ones.

However, in terms of the possible spread of the virus, this is arisky activity, and it is good to be cautious about it. There are no measures that would potentially affect St. Nicholas, respectively St. Nicholas events at the moment.

However, the general measure on the restriction of the free movement of persons implies that only family members will be able to do the devil, St. Nicholas or the angel.

The government measure can change until 5.12. 2020according to PES 3 matrice. When PES 3is implicated, there isno ban on the free movement of persons.

In case of avisit of the Devil, St. Nicholas and Angel at your home, it is recommended, if possible, that the meeting takes place outside.

If it will be possible to hold social events with aSt. Nicholas theme, please observe the general Wear Z(face masks - social distance - disinfect your hands) when participating in the events. This will prevent the virus from spreading and help protect yourself and your surroundings.

7a.title: COVID-Culture II
7a.content:
1) One-time bonus of CZK 60,000 for self-employed individuals in the culture sector.

Validity
